# ChangeLog for net-misc/networkmanager
# Copyright 1999-2015 Gentoo Foundation; Distributed under the GPL v2
# $Header: /var/cvsroot/gentoo-x86/net-misc/networkmanager/ChangeLog,v 1.233 2015/03/15 13:32:08 pacho Exp $

  15 Mar 2015; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  x86 stable, bug 534012

  15 Mar 2015; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  ppc64 stable, bug 534012

  15 Mar 2015; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  ppc stable, bug 534012

  14 Mar 2015; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  amd64 stable, bug 534012

  03 Mar 2015; Yixun Lan <dlan@gentoo.org> networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  add arm64 support, tested on A53 board

  18 Feb 2015; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> metadata.xml,
  networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  Don't install empty /var/run (#539400 by Jan Vesely)

  08 Feb 2015; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org> networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  arm stable, bug #536694

  27 Jan 2015; Anthony G. Basile <blueness@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild, networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  Keyword ~ppc ~ppc64, bug #523468

  25 Jan 2015; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  Add bug reference

  25 Jan 2015; Rémi Cardona <remi@gentoo.org> networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild,
  +files/networkmanager-1.0.0-remove-bashisms.patch:
  Fix build with /bin/sh != bash, see bug #536540.

  23 Jan 2015; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  gdbus-codegen is using at build time (#537398 by Reuben Martin)

*networkmanager-1.0.0 (10 Jan 2015)

  10 Jan 2015; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  +files/networkmanager-1.0.0-find-helpers.patch,
  +files/networkmanager-1.0.0-lto-switch.patch, +networkmanager-1.0.0.ebuild:
  Version bump

  08 Jan 2015; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild:
  net-dialup/rp-pppoe is needed by upstream to workaround a kernel problem
  (#536002 by Malte Starostik)

  01 Jan 2015; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild:
  arm stable, bug #529964

  19 Dec 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild:
  amd64 stable, bug 529964

  18 Dec 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild:
  x86 stable, bug 529964

  15 Dec 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild:
  NM shows lots of errors making nmcli neither unusable, bug #528748 (by Alex
  Brandt), upstream bug #690457, add a warning then.

  09 Dec 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild:
  Readd upstream bug reference

  01 Dec 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  -files/01-org.freedesktop.NetworkManager.settings.modify.system.pkla,
  -files/10-openrc-status-r3,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.2.0-init-provide-net-r1.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.2.0-pre-sleep.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.4.0-dhclient-ipv6.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.4.0-fix-quote-handling.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.4.0-force-libnl1.1-r1.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.4.0-ip_ppp.h.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.4.0-ipv6-route.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.4.0-libnm-glib-ensure_inited.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.4.0-libnm-glib-init-gerror.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.4.0-nl80211-encryption-caps.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.4.0-wifi-kernel-api.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.6.0-daemon-signals.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.7.995-pre-sleep.patch,
  -files/networkmanager-0.9.8.2-allow-new-dhcpcd.patch,
  -networkmanager-0.9.10.0-r1.ebuild, -networkmanager-0.9.10.0.ebuild,
  -networkmanager-0.9.6.4.ebuild, metadata.xml:
  drop old

  30 Nov 2014; Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild:
  Use python-any-r1 for the Python dep.

  27 Nov 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild:
  Make the messages a bit more clear

  26 Nov 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild:
  Update warning as it's now not systemd specific and having 'ifnet' is no
  longer fatal

*networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101 (01 Nov 2014)

  01 Nov 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  +networkmanager-0.9.10.1_pre20141101.ebuild:
  Add new snapshot including a ton of bugfixes, also this won't fail to start if
  ifnet plugin is not found and, then, migration will be less painful.

  31 Oct 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.10.0-r1.ebuild:
  Add reference to upstream bug report

  23 Oct 2014; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.10.0-r1.ebuild:
  add ~arm, bug #523468

  21 Oct 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.10.0-r1.ebuild:
  Fix the check for ifnet plugin in config

  16 Oct 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.10.0-r1.ebuild:
  Add a comment with more information

*networkmanager-0.9.10.0-r1 (13 Oct 2014)

  13 Oct 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  +files/networkmanager-0.9.10.0-arpingpath.patch,
  +networkmanager-0.9.10.0-r1.ebuild:
  Ifnet plugin is now disabled because of it being unattended and unmaintained
  for a long time, leading to some unfixed bugs and new problems appearing
  (#443596, #458274, #493370, #498372, #523700). If some day somebody volunteers
  for fixing/maintaining that plugin and forwarding all that fixes to upstream
  it could be re-enabled of course. Append configure option regarding systemd
  unit files install path only when systemd support is enabled to prevent
  HAVE_SYSTEMD to be true (#524534 by Konstantin Ivanov). Ensure arping is found
  (#523632 by Kobboi).

  11 Oct 2014; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.8.10-r1.ebuild:
  arm stable, bug #512012

  23 Sep 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.10.0.ebuild:
  x86 keyword, bug #523468

*networkmanager-0.9.10.0 (22 Sep 2014)

  22 Sep 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +networkmanager-0.9.10.0.ebuild,
  -networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild, metadata.xml:
  Version bump, default to dhclient instead of dhcpcd (#493732), set proper pppd
  plugindir (#519986 by Clemente Aguiar, Sergey Popov, Agostino Sarubbo and
  others), remove wimax support (#522822 by Dion Moult), drop old.

  21 Aug 2014; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.8.10-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for ppc64, wrt bug #512012

  28 Jul 2014; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.8.10-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for ppc, wrt bug #512012

  24 Jul 2014; Samuli Suominen <ssuominen@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.6.4.ebuild, networkmanager-0.9.8.10-r1.ebuild,
  networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  Pull in virtual/libgudev with := for automatic rebuild. Pull in virtual/udev
  as a RDEPEND. Use get_udevdir instead of the deprecated udev_get_udevdir.

  23 Jul 2014; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.8.10-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for x86, wrt bug #512012

  22 Jul 2014; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.8.10-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for amd64, wrt bug #512912

*networkmanager-0.9.8.10-r1 (16 Jun 2014)

  16 Jun 2014; Maciej Mrozowski <reavertm@gentoo.org>
  +files/networkmanager-0.9.8.9-fix-crash-on-wifi-rescan.patch,
  +networkmanager-0.9.8.10-r1.ebuild, -networkmanager-0.9.8.10.ebuild:
  Apply upstream patch for crash on Wifi re-scan.

  31 May 2014; Samuli Suominen <ssuominen@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.8.10.ebuild, networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  Allow falling back to sys-power/upower-pm-utils.

*networkmanager-0.9.8.10 (27 Apr 2014)

  27 Apr 2014; Gilles Dartiguelongue <eva@gentoo.org>
  +networkmanager-0.9.8.10.ebuild:
  Version bump for Gnome 3.12.

  29 Mar 2014; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  systemd now has subslots

  06 Mar 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  Enable modemmanager support to allow 3G USB modems to work by default instead
  of failing silently, also needed by latest gnome-control-center

  01 Mar 2014; Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.6.4.ebuild,
  networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  Update libgcrypt dep to use slot :0.

  22 Feb 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  Fix wrong commit, bug 502160

  22 Feb 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  arch stable, bug 888

  08 Dec 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  x86 stable, bug #478252

  30 Nov 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  amd64 stable, bug #478252

  15 Nov 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> -networkmanager-0.9.8.4.ebuild,
  -networkmanager-0.9.8.6.ebuild, networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  Fix grep invocation (#491284 by Rodolphe Rocca), drop old.

  12 Oct 2013; Mike Auty <ikelos@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.6.ebuild,
  networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild, metadata.xml:
  Clarify the wifi USE flag description and fix minor syntax issue in recent
  ebuilds.

  10 Oct 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  Add a wifi USE flag to pull in wpa_supplicant only for that case (#473180 by
  Marien Zwart)

*networkmanager-0.9.8.8 (10 Oct 2013)

  10 Oct 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +networkmanager-0.9.8.8.ebuild:
  Version bump

  06 Oct 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.6.ebuild:
  Add a warning for people having a NetworkManager.conf that loads ifnet plugin
  preserved for some reason (#485658#c10 by Dennis Schridde)

*networkmanager-0.9.8.6 (05 Oct 2013)

  05 Oct 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +networkmanager-0.9.8.6.ebuild,
  -networkmanager-0.9.6.4-r1.ebuild, -networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r3.ebuild:
  Version bump, use keyfile plugin instead of ifnet for systemd to prevent
  collisions and problems like bug #485658

  01 Oct 2013; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.6.4.ebuild, networkmanager-0.9.6.4-r1.ebuild,
  networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r3.ebuild, networkmanager-0.9.8.4.ebuild:
  Depend on dnsmasq[dhcp] for connection sharing (bug #475760, thanks to
  Ronald).

*networkmanager-0.9.8.4 (15 Sep 2013)

  15 Sep 2013; Alexandre Rostovtsev <tetromino@gentoo.org>
  -networkmanager-0.9.8.2.ebuild, -networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r2.ebuild,
  +networkmanager-0.9.8.4.ebuild, -files/10-openrc-status-r2,
  +files/networkmanager-0.9.8.4-pre-sleep.patch:
  Version bump, lots of bugs fixed. "systemctl enable NetworkManager" now
  properly enables NetworkManager-dispatcher (bug #477086). Drop old.

  25 Jul 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r3.ebuild:
  Refix completion dir using eclass (#477820 by Alexander Tsoy and poncho)

  19 Jul 2013; Jonathan Callen <abcd@gentoo.org>
  networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r3.ebuild:
  Fix the deps for >=dhcpcd-6 support

*networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r3 (19 Jul 2013)

  19 Jul 2013; Jonathan Callen <abcd@gentoo.org>
  +files/networkmanager-0.9.8.2-allow-new-dhcpcd.patch,
  +networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r3.ebuild, networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r2.ebuild:
  Add missing eutils inherits; add patch and bump to allow building against
  dhcpcd 6.x (previously silently failed to use dhcpcd, but still compiled and
  installed)

*networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r2 (15 Jul 2013)

  15 Jul 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r2.ebuild,
  -files/0001-core-runtime-detect-logind-and-ConsoleKit-3.patch,
  -networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r1.ebuild:
  Revision bump dropping runtime detect of logind as we won't be able to support
  logind without systemd being running, and this keeps us more close to upstream
  (preventing us from hitting any hypothetical problems that could arise from it
  until accepted by upstream). Also force dhcpcd < 6 until upstream confirms
  updating configure check is enough to properly work with newer versions.

  14 Jul 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r1.ebuild:
  Add missing eautoreconf call

  14 Jul 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org>
  +files/0001-core-runtime-detect-logind-and-ConsoleKit-3.patch:
  Add missing patch (thanks to shiznix for reporting via IRC)

*networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r1 (13 Jul 2013)

  13 Jul 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +files/10-openrc-status-r4,
  +networkmanager-0.9.8.2-r1.ebuild:
  Inherit some changes from systemd-love to make it more systemd friendly

  16 Jun 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> -networkmanager-0.9.8.0.ebuild,
  -networkmanager-9999.ebuild, metadata.xml:
  Drop old, gnome team will take this, drop live version as they are maintained
  in gnome-overlay in general.

*networkmanager-0.9.8.2 (10 Jun 2013)

  10 Jun 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +networkmanager-0.9.8.2.ebuild,
  -networkmanager-0.9.4.0-r6.ebuild, -networkmanager-0.9.7.995.ebuild:
  Version bump, drop old

  18 May 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> networkmanager-0.9.8.0.ebuild:
  Add some fixes to the ebuild and fix bash-completion locations (#465100 by
  poncho)

*networkmanager-0.9.8.0 (28 Mar 2013)

  28 Mar 2013; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +networkmanager-0.9.8.0.ebuild:
  Version bump for Gnome 3.8

